cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper addresses the problem of temporal action localization in videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a novel loss function, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
